HEADWORD: Wanger
<hw>Wang"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>wangere</ets>. See 1st <er>Wang</er>.]</ety> <def>A pillow for the
cheek; a pillow.</def> <mark>[Obs. & R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His bright helm was his <qex>wanger</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wanghee</ent>⟦br⟧
